Three days after Eskom put acting CE Matshela Koko on leave to probe allegations that a company partly owned by his stepdaughter was awarded enormous contracts, the electricity producer sneaked the company in question onto the Eskom supplier database. And as late as last week, Eskom gifted Impulse with more new contracts, despite its relationship with the supplier still being under investigation. This would appear to be a post facto attempt by Eskom to correct a breach in which Impulse was awarded contracts by a division headed by Koko before it was included in the panel of suppliers. If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link below to go to the full article: Eskom ‘pulls a fast one’ with Impulse If you would like to subscribe  to BusinessLIVE Premium to read the full story, please click here to subscribe. * Premium content is not yet available on the app. Please use the desktop site to subscribe.